<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 4:55PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Sheridan County
through 600 PM MDT...
At 455 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Westby, or 20 miles northeast of Plentywood,
moving southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Plentywood, Medicine Lake, Westby, Outlook, Reserve, Raymond, Dagmar,
Dooley, Antelope, Comertown and Coalridge.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
